--------<br>
I have a few ideas i'm going to throw out.<br>
<br>
First, a reservation is for the entire plane and every mob therein with no exceptions. If a guild can't do the big boss's, then that belongs to the next raid. If say a guild wants the boss and he's not being taken down, they can be allowed to do the boss but only if there is enough time to allow for a respawn for that next raid that may want the boss. It's basically this, if a guild/organizer signs up for a plane, they have a right to the boss. They do not have the right to deal the boss away from another raid. Any days where that plane is not reserved, those days are FFA or FCFS but mobs are only taken if there is enough time to allow for that mob to respawn for the next reserved raid.<br>
<br>
This should go for Air, Fear and Hate for sure. I think PoG should be added but i'm open.<br>
<br>
It is the responsibility of each guild/organizer to check the board and this &quot;we never check the board&quot; excuse is so lame and insulting. <br>
<br>
Sheebla  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulanaesoulsease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulanae Soulsease</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 395<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 7:51:01 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.wwa.com/~danas/Kulanae4.jpg height=158 width=119></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Reservation System idea</span><hr size=1> I agree that a planer reservation entitles you to everything that is up in the plane for that night.  And in so reserving said plane you have a right to do with that resource whatever you wish.  If your there for armor and leave the bosses, so be it.  If you are there for Bosses and they are not up, leave the plane empty or pass it to another guild for a pickup raid.<br>
<br>
I cannot support the idea that gods are reserved by reserving the plane however.  It has never been that way in the past and I really don't think it should be that way now. I also don't honestly see any viable way of reserving Gods or I would post my own suggestion. Ideally if such a system for God reservations were in place it would likely need to happen on weekends when there is sufficient time to allow one raid to clear as much of the plane as they desire, and then allow the God/Boss raid to clear what they have reserved.  This would still allow for respawn of the plane for the next days raid, and the 7 day respawn of the God makes it likely that a weekend system could continue.<br>
<br>
The idea for reservations was brought about as a means of easing tensions among Brellians in their desire for contended zones/MOB's.  As PoG is currently not a contentious zone I feel there is no need to add it as a reserved zone at this time.  But clearly it should continue to be monitored and if it's status changes then it should be considered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usheebla1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheebla1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 9:33:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re</span><hr size=1> So, basically, if I even want a chance at God items that drop off any of these mobs, I have to join SR or Watchers?  Is that the case?  Please explain to me how I can get a chance at these wonderful things when I hear that a guild goes to Fear and takes down CT, then goes to Fear because there bored.  One guild can just sit back and go around killing bosses while other guilds go begging.  I'll tell you this, there is a lot of discontent out there and if there is not a fair shake for everyone, there will be a backlash.  This is not a threat, it's basic a human characteristic.  If I reserve a plane, just do me the courtesy of leaving me the whole plane.  I don't think that farming the Bosses is fair and that is where were headed.<br>
<br>
Sheebla  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 814<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 9:47:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> Harpers killed all 3 golems and got God loot.  So have many other raids.  The only mobs that no one has been able to take down and have asked for help from SR/Watchers is Draco and CT.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So, basically, if I even want a chance at God items that drop off any of these mobs, I have to join SR or Watchers? Is that the case? Please explain to me how I can get a chance at these wonderful things <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
